<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 15 at 3:40AM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>North winds of 10 to around 15 mph will produce wind chill values
of 12 below zero to 7 below zero. There will be a few locations
where the wind chill may be as low as 17 below zero early this
morning. Otherwise below zero wind chill values will remain into
late this morning.
If you need to be outside, be prepared for the wind and cold, and
dress in layers and wear a hat, heavy coat, as well as gloves or
mittens. Frostbite can occur in a short amount of time, so dress
in layers and make sure all exposed skin is protected.</description>
